//! TML Core Library
//!
//! Fundamental behaviors and types that form the foundation of the TML language.
//!
//! This library provides the core building blocks that the standard library and
//! user code depends on. It includes behaviors for comparison, formatting, memory
//! management, iteration, and async programming.
//!
//! # Core Behaviors
//!
//! | Module | Contents |
//! |--------|----------|
//! | [`clone`] | `Duplicate`, `Copy` behaviors for cloning and copying values |
//! | [`cmp`] | `Ordering`, `PartialEq`, `Eq`, `PartialOrd`, `Ord` for comparing values |
//! | [`ops`] | Operator overloading: `Add`, `Sub`, `Mul`, `Div`, `Rem`, `Neg`, `Not`, `Index`, etc. |
//! | [`default`] | `Default` behavior for types with default values |
//! | [`fmt`] | `Display`, `Debug` behaviors for formatting and debugging |
//!
//! # Type Conversions
//!
//! | Module | Contents |
//! |--------|----------|
//! | [`convert`] | `From`, `Into`, `TryFrom`, `TryInto`, `AsRef`, `AsMut` for conversions |
//! | [`hash`] | `Hash` behavior for hashable types and `Hasher` trait |
//!
//! # Markers and Safety
//!
//! | Module | Contents |
//! |--------|----------|
//! | [`marker`] | `Send`, `Sync`, `Sized`, `Unpin` marker behaviors |
//! | [`pin`] | `Pin` type and `Unpin` behavior for pinned memory locations |
//!
//! # Memory and Allocation
//!
//! | Module | Contents |
//! |--------|----------|
//! | [`mem`] | `size_of`, `swap`, `replace`, `forget`, `ManuallyDrop` utilities |
//! | [`cell`] | Interior mutability: `Cell`, `RefCell`, `OnceCell`, `LazyCell` |
//! | [`ptr`] | Raw pointer operations, `NonNull`, pointer arithmetic |
//! | [`alloc`] | Memory allocation: `Layout`, `Allocator`, `GlobalAlloc` |
//! | [`arena`] | `Arena` allocator for fast bump-pointer allocation |
//! | [`pool`] | `Pool[T]` for object pooling with lock-free free lists |
//! | [`soo`] | Small Object Optimization: `SmallVec`, `SmallString`, `SmallBox` |
//! | [`cache`] | Cache-friendly layouts: `CacheAligned`, `Padded`, `SoaVec` |
//!
//! # Collections and Iteration
//!
//! | Module | Contents |
//! |--------|----------|
//! | [`iter`] | `Iterator`, `IntoIterator`, `FromIterator`, and 30+ adapters |
//! | [`slice`] | Slice operations: `sort`, `binary_search`, `split`, `windows`, etc. |
//! | [`array`] | Fixed-size array utilities: `from_fn`, `repeat`, `zip`, `map` |
//! | [`collections`] | Behavior impls for `List`, `HashMap`, `Vec` (re-exports std) |
//!
//! # String and Character Handling
//!
//! | Module | Contents |
//! |--------|----------|
//! | [`str`] | String manipulation and operations |
//! | [`bstr`] | `ByteStr` for non-UTF-8 byte strings |
//! | [`char`] | `Char` (Unicode scalar value), `from_u32`, `DecodeUtf16` |
//! | [`ascii`] | `AsciiChar`, ASCII character classification and escaping |
//! | [`unicode`] | Unicode 15.1.0 classification, case conversion, properties |
//! | [`encoding`] | Base64, hex, percent-encoding, base32, base85 |
//!
//! # Optional and Error Handling
//!
//! | Module | Contents |
//! |--------|----------|
//! | [`option`] | `Maybe[T]` enhanced methods and combinators |
//! | [`result`] | `Outcome[T, E]` enhanced methods and combinators |
//! | [`error`] | `Error` behavior, `SimpleError`, `IoError`, `ParseError` |
//!
//! # Ownership and Borrowing
//!
//! | Module | Contents |
//! |--------|----------|
//! | [`borrow`] | `Borrow`, `BorrowMut`, `ToOwned`, `Cow` for flexible borrowing |
//! | [`sync`] | Raw atomic operations, memory fences, spinlocks |
//!
//! # Async Programming
//!
//! | Module | Contents |
//! |--------|----------|
//! | [`task`] | `Poll`, `Context`, `Waker` â€” async task primitives |
//! | [`future`] | `Future` behavior and combinators |
//! | [`async_iter`] | `AsyncIterator` for async streams |
//!
//! # Utility Types
//!
//! | Module | Contents |
//! |--------|----------|
//! | [`range`] | `Range`, `RangeInclusive`, `RangeFrom`, `RangeTo`, `RangeFull` |
//! | [`num`] | `Zero`, `One`, `Bounded`, `Saturating`, `Wrapping`, `NonZero` |
//! | [`time`] | `Duration` type for time measurements |
//! | [`tuple`] | Tuple implementations: `Clone`, `PartialEq`, `Ord`, etc. |
//! | [`any`] | `TypeId`, `Any` for runtime type identification |
//! | [`reflect`] | `TypeInfo`, `FieldInfo`, `Reflect` behavior for reflection |
//! | [`simd`] | Portable SIMD: `I32x4`, `F32x4`, `I64x2`, etc. |
//! | [`intrinsics`] | Compiler intrinsics for type metadata and operations |

